The Olympia-Einkaufszentrum (OEZ) is a shopping mall opened in 1972. It is located in the Moosach district of Munich, Germany. The name comes from the simultaneous construction of the adjacent home of the press for the Summer Olympics in 1972. 1993/94 was extended and modernization according to the plans of the Munich architects Hans Baumgarten and Curt O. Schaller.
The sales area of the OEZ, which belongs to the ECE Project Management, amounts to 56,000 m2. Two levels hold approximately 135 shops, three department stores, major clothing stores, grocery stores, service outlets, restaurants and cafes are located. In addition, there are 2,400 parking spaces available.
Since the 31 October 2004, the OEZ location on Hanauerstrae is accessible by U1 and since October 28, 2007, it is also accessible with the U3, subway station Olympia-Einkaufszentrum.

